article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 83, Jacksonville St. 60
article.story: MARTIN, Tenn. (AP) -- Cleve Woodfork scored 20 points and Tennessee-Martin shot a season-high 59.5 percent from the floor to beat Jacksonville State 83-60 on Saturday night. The Skyhawks (6-16, 4-8 Ohio Valley Conference) were 25-and-42 from the floor and shot 47 percent from beyond the arc. Tennessee-Martin took the lead early in the first half and sent the Gamecocks (5-16, 3-9) into halftime up 34-27. Will Ginn scored 18 points and Harold Crow added 17 for Jacksonville State, which shot 38 percent from the floor. The Gamecocks never came closer than five points behind at 14:12 in the second half. Woodfork extended the lead in the second half to 24 when he tipped in a missed 3-pointer by McClenon Tolliver at 4:07. Gerald Robinson added 16 points with four 3-pointers for Tennessee-Martin and Will Lewis scored 11 with eight rebounds.
